[2026-03-08T02:59:34Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UrbVxAhg4J7XmRgi48FVn7","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Orchestration Flow Analysis - Complete Summary\n\nBased on my thorough review of the codebase, here's the complete orchestration flow and the mechanisms that could result in \"No ready work found\":\n\n### 1. **Top-Level Entry Points**\n\n#### CLI Command (`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go:396-408`)\n```go\nfunc cmdOrchestrate(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient) {\n    cwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n    resp, err := client.Orchestrate(ctx, &pb.OrchestrateRequest{ProjectDir: cwd})\n    if err != nil {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n    if resp.Dispatched == 0 {\n        fmt.Println(\"No ready work found.\")  // <-- This message\n    } else {\n        fmt.Printf(\"Dispatched %d run(s).\\n\", resp.Dispatched)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe \"No ready work found\" message is printed when `resp.Dispatched == 0` is returned from the gRPC Orchestrate call.\n\n#### gRPC Handler (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go:668-677`)\n```go\nfunc (s *ClocheServer) Orchestrate(ctx context.Context, req *pb.OrchestrateRequest) (*pb.OrchestrateResponse, error) {\n    if s.orchestrateFn == nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"orchestrator not configured\")\n    }\n    dispatched, err := s.orchestrateFn(ctx, req.ProjectDir)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"orchestration failed: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return &pb.OrchestrateResponse{Dispatched: int32(dispatched)}, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 2. **Core Orchestrator Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`)\n\n#### Initialization - Project Registration (`cmd/cloched/main.go:226-286`)\n- At daemon startup, `initOrchestrator()` scans all projects and registers those with `orchestration.enabled = true` in their `.cloche/config.toml`\n- Each project is registered with:\n  - Directory path\n  - Workflow name (defaults to \"develop\")\n  - Concurrency limit (defaults to 1)\n  - A **TaskTracker** instance (Beads adapter by default)\n\n#### Main Run Method (`orchestrator.go:169-300`)\n```go\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) Run(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) (int, error)\n```\n\n**Flow:**\n1. **Check concurrency limits** (lines 170-186)\n   - Lock the orchestrator mutex\n   - Get ProjectConfig for the directory\n   - Check if `pc.Enabled == true`\n   - Calculate available slots: `available = concurrency - inFlight`\n   - If `available <= 0`, return 0 (no work dispatched)\n\n2. **Query ready tasks** (lines 188-191)\n   - Call `pc.Tracker.ListReady(ctx, projectDir)` which:\n     - Reads `.beads/issues.jsonl`\n     - Returns only tasks with `status == \"open\"`\n     - Filters out tasks with open blocking dependencies\n     - Sorts by priority (highest first)\n   - If no tasks returned, the loop doesn't execute → return 0\n\n3. **Dispatch available tasks** (lines 203-297)\n   - For each ready task, up to the available concurrency slots:\n     - Check if task is already in-flight (dedup check at lines 207-213)\n     - Call `Claim(taskID)` to mark it as `in_progress` in beads\n     - Either use host.cloche path or fallback to promptGen → dispatch\n     - Track the run-task mapping\n     - Increment in-flight counter\n\n4. **Return dispatch count**\n   - Returns total number of runs dispatched (0 if none)\n\n### 3. **Task Tracking - Beads Integration** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/beads/tracker.go`)\n\n#### ListReady Method (lines 54-91)\n```go\nfunc (t *Tracker) ListReady(_ context.Context, project string) ([]ports.TrackerTask, error) {\n    issues, err := readIssuesFromFile(t.beadsPath())\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    statusByID := make(map[string]string, len(issues))\n    for _, iss := range issues {\n        statusByID[iss.ID] = iss.Status\n    }\n\n    var tasks []ports.TrackerTask\n    for _, iss := range issues {\n        if iss.Status != \"open\" {\n            continue\n        }\n        if hasOpenBlockers(iss, statusByID) {\n            continue\n        }\n        tasks = append(tasks, ports.TrackerTask{...})\n    }\n\n    sort.Slice(tasks, func(i, j int) bool {\n        return tasks[i].Priority > tasks[j].Priority\n    })\n\n    return tasks, nil\n}\n```\n\n**Critical checks:**\n- Line 71: Tasks must have `status == \"open\"`\n- Line 74: Tasks with open blockers are filtered out via `hasOpenBlockers()` (lines 94-102)\n- Ordered by priority (descending)\n\n#### hasOpenBlockers (lines 94-102)\n```go\nfunc hasOpenBlockers(iss issue, statusByID map[string]string) bool {\n    for _, dep := range iss.Dependencies {\n        depStatus := statusByID[dep.DependsOnID]\n        if depStatus != \"closed\" {\n            return true\n        }\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\n**Issue:** A blocker dependency must have `status == \"closed\"` to be considered satisfied. Any other status (`open`, `in_progress`, `tombstone`, undefined) blocks the task.\n\n#### In-Flight Tracking (lines 140-165)\n```go\n// Orchestrator tracks inFlightTaskSet: projectDir → set of taskIDs currently being processed\n// Dedup check prevents re-dispatching same task:\nalreadyRunning := o.isTaskInFlight(projectDir, task.ID)\nif alreadyRunning {\n    log.Printf(\"orchestrator: skipping task %s (already in flight)\", task.ID)\n    continue\n}\n```\n\n### 4. **Concurrency Management** (`orchestrator.go`)\n\n#### Status Tracking\n```go\ntype Orchestrator struct {\n    // ...\n    inFlight        map[string]int          // projectDir → count of in-flight runs\n    inFlightTasks   map[string]string       // runID → taskID mapping\n    inFlightTaskSet map[string]map[string]bool // projectDir → set of taskIDs in flight\n}\n```\n\n#### Run Completion Handler (`orchestrator.go:327-350`)\n```go\nfunc (o *Orchestrator) OnRunComplete(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, runID string, state domain.RunState) {\n    // 1. Untrack the task and decrement in-flight counter\n    taskID := o.untrackTask(projectDir, runID)\n    if o.inFlight[projectDir] > 0 {\n        o.inFlight[projectDir]--\n    }\n\n    // 2. Close or fail the task in the tracker\n    if taskID != \"\" && pc != nil {\n        if state == domain.RunStateSucceeded {\n            _ = pc.Tracker.Complete(ctx, taskID)  // Sets status to \"closed\"\n        } else {\n            _ = pc.Tracker.Fail(ctx, taskID)      // Sets status back to \"open\"\n        }\n    }\n\n    // 3. Trigger a new orchestration cycle\n    if _, err := o.Run(ctx, projectDir); err != nil {\n        log.Printf(\"orchestrator: post-completion trigger failed for %s: %v\", projectDir, err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 5. **Why \"No Ready Work Found\" Occurs**\n\n#### Scenario A: No Tasks at All\n- `.beads/issues.jsonl` file is empty or contains no `open` tasks\n- ListReady returns empty slice\n- Orchestrator.Run() returns 0\n\n#### Scenario B: All Tasks Blocked\n- Open tasks exist but ALL have unsatisfied blocking dependencies\n- `hasOpenBlockers()` returns true for every task\n- ListReady returns empty slice\n- Orchestrator.Run() returns 0\n\n#### Scenario C: Concurrency Limit Reached\n- All slots filled with in-flight runs\n- `available = concurrency - inFlight` = 0 or negative\n- Early return at line 184-185: `return 0, nil`\n- No ListReady call happens\n\n#### Scenario D: All Ready Tasks Already In-Flight\n- Open tasks with satisfied dependencies exist\n- All of them have runIDs in `inFlightTaskSet[projectDir]`\n- Dedup check skips all of them (lines 207-213)\n- Returns 0 dispatched\n\n### 6. **Configuration & Defaults**\n\n#### Per-Project Settings (`/workspace/internal/config/config.go`)\n```go\ntype OrchestrationConfig struct {\n    Enabled     bool   `toml:\"enabled\"`\n    Tracker     string `toml:\"tracker\"`\n    Concurrency int    `toml:\"concurrency\"`\n    Workflow    string `toml:\"workflow\"`\n}\n\n// Defaults (lines 48-52):\nOrchestration: OrchestrationConfig{\n    Tracker:     \"beads\",\n    Concurrency: 1,\n    Workflow:    \"develop\",\n},\n```\n\nSettings loaded from `.cloche/config.toml` via `config.Load(projectDir)`.\n\n#### Runtime Override\n- Via web dashboard API: `/api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency`\n- Updates `ProjectConfig.Concurrency` in-memory (lines 107-113)\n\n### 7. **Key Mechanisms & Entry Points**\n\n| Component | File | Purpose |\n|-----------|------|---------|\n| **CLI orchestrate** | `cmd/cloche/main.go:396-408` | User-facing command that prints \"No ready work found\" |\n| **gRPC Orchestrate** | `internal/adapters/grpc/server.go:668-677` | RPC handler that returns dispatch count |\n| **Orchestrator.Run** | `internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go:169-300` | Core logic: checks concurrency, lists ready tasks, dispatches runs |\n| **Orchestrator.OnRunComplete** | `internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go:327-350` | Callback on run finish: updates task status, triggers next cycle |\n| **Beads ListReady** | `internal/adapters/beads/tracker.go:54-91` | Returns open tasks with no blocked dependencies, sorted by priority |\n| **hasOpenBlockers** | `internal/adapters/beads/tracker.go:94-102` | Dependency filtering: blocks if any dependent has status ≠ \"closed\" |\n| **In-Flight Tracking** | `internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go:140-165` | Deduplication: prevents re-dispatching same task ID |\n| **Project Registration** | `cmd/cloched/main.go:226-286` | Startup scan: registers projects with `orchestration.enabled = true` |\n| **Config Loading** | `internal/config/config.go:56-73` | Reads `.cloche/config.toml` for per-project settings |\n\n### 8. **Absolute File Paths**\n\nAll key files relevant to orchestration flow:\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI entry point\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` - Daemon initialization\n- `/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go` - Core orchestrator\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/beads/tracker.go` - Task tracker (Beads)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - gRPC server\n- `/workspace/internal/config/config.go` - Configuration system\n- `/workspace/.beads/issues.jsonl` - Task database (JSONL format)\n- `/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator_test.go` - Test suite\n\nThe orchestration system is well-designed with proper concurrency controls, deduplication, dependency checking, and task lifecycle management. The \"No ready work found\" message can occur legitimately in several scenarios, but the underlying logic is sound."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a524728358a9ce8cd (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 80689\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 46267</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be3855ff-2535-428a-8a0c-d975245212ae","uuid":"4cdbcf1a-726a-4381-8b24-833298af5adc","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the orchestration flow in this Go project. Find and read:\n1. The orchestrator code (likely in internal/evolution/orchestrator.go)\n2. The gRPC handler for orchestrate commands (likely in internal/adapters/web/handler.go)\n3. The beads/issues tracker (look for .beads/issues.jsonl and any Go code that reads it)\n4. Any \"No ready work found\" or \"no ready work\" message in the codebase\n5. The inFlight tracking mechanism\n6. The concurrency setting handling\n7. The `bd list` command or equivalent that shows open tasks\n\nBe very thorough - read the full files, not just snippets. I need to understand why orchestrate would return \"No ready work found\" when there are open unblocked tasks.","agentId":"a524728358a9ce8cd","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Orchestration Flow Analysis - Complete Summary\n\nBased on my thorough review of the codebase, here's the complete orchestrati