eb dashboard's Trigger Orchestrator button (POST /api/projects/{name}/trigger) is a stub that returns 202 without calling the orchestrator. Wire it up:\\n\\n1. Add an orchestrateFn field (func(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) (int, error)) to the web Handler struct.\\n2. Add a WithOrchestrateFunc HandlerOption to set it.\\n3. In handleAPITriggerOrchestrator, resolve the project name to its directory (via the run store's ListProjects), call orchestrateFn, and return the dispatched count or an error.\\n4. In cmd/cloched/main.go, pass web.WithOrchestrateFunc(...) when constructing the web handler, using the same function wired to the gRPC server's SetOrchestrateFunc.\\n5. Add a unit test in handler_test.go verifying the trigger endpoint calls the function and returns the count.\\n6. If orchestrateFn is nil, return 501 Not Implemented.\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"estimated_minutes\":15,\"created_at\":\"2026-03-03T19:07:34.595694255-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-04T17:03:00.48870097-08:00\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-03-04T17:03:00.48870097-08:00\",\"close_reason\":\"Closed\",\"labels\":[\"orchestrator\",\"web\"]}\n{\"id\":\"cloche-mk9\",\"title\":\"Chore: rename .cloche/config to .cloche/config.toml in cloche project\",\"description\":\"After cloche-2cc merges and is installed, the daemon will look for .cloche/config.toml. Rename our own project's config file to match, verify the daemon reads it correctly, and commit the rename.\",\"acceptance_criteria\":\"- .cloche/config.toml exists with the same contents as the old .cloche/config\\n- .cloche/config is deleted\\n- cloched reads orchestration settings correctly after restart\",\"status\":\"closed\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"lucas@perfectlunacy.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T11:42:26.677558038-08:00\",\"created_by\":\"lucas\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T14:24:45.211015766-08:00\",\"closed_a