[2026-03-08T02:59:34Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MaibocndrBhJJkDYyY7ueS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DWU72Dc2o9z2gHtbm3B9A1","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('.beads/issues.jsonl') as f:\n    seen = {}\n    for line in f:\n        line = line.strip()\n        if not line: continue\n        try:\n            iss = json.loads(line)\n        except: continue\n        if iss.get('status') == 'tombstone':\n            seen.pop(iss['id'], None)\n            continue\n        seen[iss['id']] = iss\n    \n    for iss in seen.values():\n        if iss['status'] in ('open', 'in_progress'):\n            deps = iss.get('dependencies', [])\n            dep_ids = [d['depends_on_id'] for d in deps]\n            dep_statuses = []\n            for did in dep_ids:\n                if did in seen:\n                    dep_statuses.append(f'{did}={seen[did][\\\"status\\\"]}')\n                else:\n                    dep_statuses.append(f'{did}=MISSING')\n            print(f'{iss[\\\"id\\\"]} status={iss[\\\"status\\\"]} priority={iss[\\\"priority\\\"]} deps=[{\\\", \\\".join(dep_statuses)}] title={iss[\\\"title\\\"][:80]}')\n\"\n","description":"List open/in_progress tasks with dependency status"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":124,"cache_read_input_tokens":48869,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":124},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be3855ff-2535-428a-8a0c-d975245212ae","uuid":"720db554-c35b-4644-b20e-25d9c32df6a8"}
[2026-03-08T02:59:34Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DWU72Dc2o9z2gHtbm3B9A1","type":"tool_result","content":"cloche-r3b status=in_progress priority=2 deps=[] title=Investigate cloche orchestrate 'No ready work found' despite open tasks","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be3855ff-2535-428a-8a0c-d975245212ae","uuid":"af48302b-9085-4f44-aa0e-fd35f8896df8","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"cloche-r3b status=in_progress priority=2 deps=[] title=Investigate cloche orchestrate 'No ready work found' despite open tasks","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
[2026-03-08T02:59:34Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01C7BjqH5kKS9K3mpRxR57jY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! There's only ONE task that's open/in_progress, and that's THIS task (cloche-r3b) which is already `in_progress`. So when `bd list` shows 4 open unblocked P2 tasks, that's not matching what the JSONL file shows now.\n\nWait - the task description says \"bd list shows 4 open, unblocked P2 tasks\". But currently I only see 1 task that's open/in_progress. The issue may have been that the tasks were previously open but got claimed and set to in_progress or closed during previous orchestration attempts.\n \nLet me trace through the JSONL history more carefully since it's append-only and the latest entry for each task ID determines its current state. The 4 open tasks mentioned in the issue description might have already been processed. The real question is why `cloche orchestrate` returns \"No ready work found\" when there should be open tasks available—I need to follow the orchestration flow to see where it's failing.\n\nThe CLI passes the current working directory as the ProjectDir to the gRPC Orchestrate call, which then runs through the orchestrator's checks for project registration, enabled status, and available concurrency before calling ListReady. The critical issue might be whether the project directory path matches exactly between what the CLI sends and what was registered in the orchestrator during initialization. The CLI only shows \"No ready work found\" when dispatched is 0 with no error—otherwise it prints the error and exits. Looking at the scenarios that produce zero dispatches: a registered but disabled project, hitting the concurrency limit, an empty ready list, or all ready tasks already in-flight and deduplicated. Since there's only one task currently in progress with concurrency set to 1, and that task is the investigation itself, the issue likely stems from when multiple tasks were open earlier.\n\nBut the user is seeing 4 open tasks in `bd list` while `cloche orchestrate` reports no work, which suggests either a timing issue or a path mismatch. The daemon registers with its startup directory, so if it started in a different location than where the user runs the command, the paths won't align and tasks won't be found. Let me check how the config loading works—it iterates through candidate directories, loads the config, checks if orchestration is enabled, and creates a tracker for that directory.\n\nThe real problem is that `ListReady` ignores the `project` argument it receives and always uses the tracker's hardcoded `projectDir` from registration time. So if the tracker was initialized with the daemon's working directory, it'll only look for tasks in that specific location, even if the CLI is pointing elsewhere.\n\nLooking at the actual issue more carefully—the task shows it was claimed and moved to in_progress, so the orchestrator is functioning for at least some tasks. The \"No ready work found\" error could stem from a few things: the daemon and CLI might be registering different project paths, the concurrency limit might be exhausted with a task already running, or all available tasks could be in a non-ready state.\n\nLet me check the configuration to see if orchestration is actually enabled.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":449,"cache_read_input_tokens":48993,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":449},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be3855ff-2535-428a-8a0c-d975245212ae","uuid":"dd3246c4-890c-4157-b505-4416a2fcf56d"}
