[2026-03-08T02:59:34Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01R7u5sbcGkF2TUYA3uYhNZs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear understanding of the bug. Let me now implement the fix. The root cause is:\n\n**When the daemon restarts, `FailStaleRuns()` marks runs as failed in SQLite, but never resets the corresponding beads tasks from `in_progress` back to `open`.** `ListReady` only returns `status == \"open\"` tasks, so `in_progress` tasks become orphaned — invisible to the orchestrator despite having no active run.\n\nI need to:\n1. Add a `RecoverStaleTasks` method to the `TaskTracker` interface and beads adapter\n2. Call it during daemon startup, after `FailStaleRuns`\n\nLet me also check if there's a way to do this within the orchestrator itself."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":414,"cache_read_input_tokens":60958,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":414},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"be3855ff-2535-428a-8a0c-d975245212ae","uuid":"991f3a7c-51a5-4710-9bd1-33da4bc7983d"}
