[2026-03-08T02:59:34Z] [llm] {"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":281698,"duration_api_ms":273842,"num_turns":36,"result":"Everything is clean. Here's a summary of the investigation and fix:\n\n## Root Cause\n\nWhen the daemon restarts (or crashes), `FailStaleRuns()` marks in-flight runs as failed in SQLite, but **never resets the corresponding beads tasks from `in_progress` back to `open`**. Since `ListReady` only returns tasks with `status == \"open\"`, these orphaned `in_progress` tasks become permanently invisible to the orchestrator — even though no run is actually processing them.\n\nThe scenario: 4 tasks were open, the orchestrator claimed them (setting status to `in_progress`), then the daemon restarted. After restart, `ListReady` returns 0 tasks (all are `in_progress`), so `cloche orchestrate` reports \"No ready work found\". Meanwhile `bd list` shows them because it displays all non-closed tasks.\n\n## Fix\n\nThree changes:\n\n1. **`ports.TaskTracker` interface** (`internal/ports/tracker.go`): Added `RecoverStaleTasks(ctx) (int, error)` method to reset orphaned `in_progress` tasks.\n\n2. **Beads adapter** (`internal/adapters/beads/tracker.go`): Implemented `RecoverStaleTasks` — scans for `in_progress` tasks and appends status updates resetting them to `open`.\n\n3. **Daemon startup** (`cmd/cloched/main.go`): Added `orch.RecoverAll()` call before `TriggerAll()`, which iterates all registered projects and calls `RecoverStaleTasks` on each tracker. The `Orchestrator.RecoverAll` method is in `internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`.\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"be3855ff-2535-428a-8a0c-d975245212ae","total_cost_usd":1.7294806500000002,"usage":{"input_tokens":2637,"cache_creation_input_tokens":68371,"cache_read_input_tokens":1674892,"output_tokens":11010,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":68371,